
[1]wretchedness

   WRETCHEDNESS, n.

   1. Extreme misery or unhappiness, either from want or sorrow; as the
   wretchedness of poor mendicants.

   We have, with the feeling, most the very memory of such wretchedness as
   our forefathers endured--

   The prodigal brought nothing to his father but his rags and
   wretchedness.

   2. Meanness; despicableness; as the wretchedness of a performance.
